00:49:42.280 --> 00:49:47.096
' But Diana and I, we're just like, 'Where is a chicken?

00:49:47.096 --> 00:49:51.395
' We're going, I mean, and to the vegans, 'Where is a good lettuce head?

00:49:51.395 --> 00:49:52.772
Where's a good cabbage?

00:49:52.772 --> 00:49:54.650
' I don't know, whatever you eat.

00:50:08.829 --> 00:50:09.119
But I like chicken myself, and I'm going to look for some chicken instead of a lettuce head for the vegans.

00:50:09.119 --> 00:50:10.133
Or some tofu.

00:50:10.133 --> 00:50:11.340
Where's some tofu?

00:50:11.340 --> 00:50:17.257
I'm just going to find something that's going to make some meat on my bones spiritually.

00:50:27.440 --> 00:50:27.859
And tofu doesn't settle with me—I'm just being real with y'all.

00:50:29.645 --> 00:50:29.908
God loves everybody.

00:50:35.350 --> 00:50:35.820
He gave me chicken to eat, too, God bless it.

00:50:35.820 --> 00:50:37.700
Chicken and dumplings!

00:50:37.700 --> 00:50:38.640
Woohoo!

00:50:38.640 --> 00:50:39.280
Whatever.

